==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
'''interpolation'''

# In music: an abrupt change of elements, with (almost immediate) continuation of the first idea. (DeLone et. al. (Eds.), 1975, chap. 1)
# In mathematics and science: the process of estimating the value of a function at a point from its values at nearby points.

